 I - TO INSTALL CDO_PRICER TOOLBOX
 *********************

 1 -Configure your system by issuing the following command in the Unix 
    directory:
    	./configure

	run ./configure 


 2 - Do in the Unix directory:
 	make 
 
        This will compile all  CDO_PRICER TOOLBOX .

3- If you want to clean object files execute the following commands
	make distclean


 II - TO RUN CDO_PRICER TOOLBOX
 *********************

Run Scilab interface in the Scilab directory

	/scilab/exec interface.sci


III-ALGORITHMS
*********************

CDO_PRICER TOOLBOX contains the following algorithm:

	1) Monte Carlo methods
	2) Monte Carlo methos with control variate
	3) Hull-White algorithm
	4) Laurent-Gregory algorithm

- In the "Src" directory you find .c source files
- "Scilab" directory containts The CDO_PRICER-scilab interface
- In "demo" directory  you find the function 'price_cdo'
used to interface with Scilab
- in "datas" you find all the data market
- "doc" contains all the documentation in html and latex


